choices.text: the formal independence itself. For a partition state, the biggest achievement should be the independence. For 20 years in Spain, Catalonia continued to grow closer to independence by storming through society. For 100 years in Panama, Panama continued to grow nearer to independence under the American colony. The biggest event for these two places is the declaration of Formal Independence. For a colony, the declaration of independence is the biggest event. For 150 years in Siam, Siam remained silent under the shadow of foreign countries. The biggest event for Siam is the formal independence. Same for intransigence. For 700 years, the Intra-Wu region developed under the Yuan Dynasty, the Ming Dynasty, the Qing Dynasty, the Japanese invasion and government transition. The biggest event for Intra-Wu history is the formal independence. The meaning of being a nation state was also inscribed into the visual standards of the state. As we can see, Siam or Intra-Wu created the national sikenni standard, which include national flags and national standards for the countries with three majestic national standards and standards for the Great Empire Siam. During the Qing Dynasty in China, the only country with official national standard was under Hai-Dui-Sond, rather than the Chinese people as a whole. Qing Dynasty drew up the very first national flag for the country of China. Although the flag looks like the Qing dynasty flag, however, the flags in the former four standardization arrangements were surprisingly different
